==English==
===Etymology===
From George Orwell's book ''1984''. A Gestapo organization responsible for monitoring all citizens and making sure they are not guilty of political dissent, or thoughtcrime.

===Noun===
'''thought police''' ''collective [[noun phrase]]''

# A group that aims to control what other people [[think]].
#:''Wiktionary sysops are on their way to becoming '''thought police'''.''
#:''My mother would make a good '''thought police'''.'' (singular usage)

====Usage note====
*Formerly a singular [[noun phrase]], '''Thought Police''' is now almost always used as a collective noun phrase with a plural verb, as in "Run, the Though Police are coming!"

